statement:
The functions \emph{f(x) = x\textsuperscript{2}} and \emph{g(x) =
x\textsuperscript{3}} are equal at \emph{x = 0} and at \emph{x = 1}.
Between \emph{x = 0} and \emph{x = 1}, for what value of \emph{x} are
their graphs furthest apart?

\begin{itemize}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item
  \textbf{(a)} \emph{x = 1/2}
\end{itemize}

\begin{itemize}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item
  \textbf{(b)} \emph{x = 1/3}
\end{itemize}

\begin{itemize}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item
  \textbf{(c)} \emph{x = 2/3}
\end{itemize}

\begin{itemize}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item
  \textbf{(d)} \emph{x = 1/4}
\end{itemize}

\begin{itemize}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item
  \textbf{(e)} \emph{x = 3/4}
\end{itemize}
